[{'id': '113516630682811569', 'type': 'image', 'url': 'https://media.mastodon.de/cache/media_attachments/files/113/516/630/682/811/569/original/3f69742a9886549b.png', 'preview_url': 'https://media.mastodon.de/cache/media_attachments/files/113/516/630/682/811/569/small/3f69742a9886549b.png', 'remote_url': 'https://s3.eu-central-2.wasabisys.com/mastodonworld/media_attachments/files/113/516/614/520/612/329/original/ce6078b5b2454b1a.png', 'preview_remote_url': None, 'text_url': None, 'meta': {'focus': {'x': 0.0, 'y': 0.0}, 'original': {'width': 679, 'height': 612, 'size': '679x612', 'aspect': 1.1094771241830066}, 'small': {'width': 506, 'height': 456, 'size': '506x456', 'aspect': 1.1096491228070176}}, 'description': "The policy — which Johnson announced in a public statement, a draft of which was first reported by The Hill — will also apply to bathrooms in House office buildings, changing rooms and locker rooms. It is unclear when he plans to publish the comments.

Under House rules, the Speaker has “general control” of facilities in the chamber, giving him the authority to issue the policy surrounding bathrooms.

“All single-sex facilities in the Capitol and House Office Buildings — such as restrooms, changing rooms, and locker rooms — are reserved for individuals of that biological sex,” Johnson said. “It is important to note that each Member office has its own private restroom, and unisex restrooms are available throughout the Capitol.”

“Women deserve women'’s only spaces,” he added.

Johnson’s statement — which was made on Transgender Day of Remembrance, recognized annually to memorialize trans people who lost their lives to anti-trans violence — comes days after Rep. Nancy Mace (R- S.C.) introduced a bill to bar transgender women from facilities on Capitol Hill that match their gender identity, a response to the election earlier this month of Rep.-elect Sarah McBride (D-Del.).", 'blurhash': 'U4R:HG00-;Rjxuj]RjWBIUofofofj[axt7j@'}, {'id': '113516630700921662', 'type': 'image', 'url': 'https://media.mastodon.de/cache/media_attachments/files/113/516/630/700/921/662/original/eb6afbb7bef6f86a.png', 'preview_url': 'https://media.mastodon.de/cache/media_attachments/files/113/516/630/700/921/662/small/eb6afbb7bef6f86a.png', 'remote_url': 'https://s3.eu-central-2.wasabisys.com/mastodonworld/media_attachments/files/113/516/615/360/096/984/original/42bc7aedd0d464f3.png', 'preview_remote_url': None, 'text_url': None, 'meta': {'focus': {'x': 0.0, 'y': 0.0}, 'original': {'width': 699, 'height': 610, 'size': '699x610', 'aspect': 1.1459016393442623}, 'small': {'width': 513, 'height': 448, 'size': '513x448', 'aspect': 1.1450892857142858}}, 'description': "McBride will be the first openly transgender person elected to Congress. Johnson’s plan to publicly announce his policy comes after the Speaker sidestepped specifics when asked about McBride earlier this week, and refused to say if he would put Mace'’s bill in the House rules package for the 119th Congress.

“I'm not going to address the plans on any of that. | just told you what I'm going to say about the issue. I'm not going to engage in this,” Johnson said at his press conference. “We don't look down upon anyone. We treat everybody with dignity and respect. That’s a principle that I've pursued my whole life, and we will take care of this issue of first impression for congress as we will any other thing. We'll provide appropriate accommodation for every member of congress.”

In a statement hours later, the Speaker told reporters “for anyone who doesn’'t know my established record on this issue, let me be unequivocally clear: a man is a man, and a woman is a woman, and a man cannot become awoman.”

“That said, | also believe that's what scripture teaches, what | just said, but | also believe we treat everybody with dignity. We can do and believe all those things at the same time,” he added.", 'blurhash': 'U3R:HH4T?bIUayt7t7M{?bj[Rjs;-;t7ofWB'}, {'id': '113516630720076713', 'type': 'image', 'url': 'https://media.mastodon.de/cache/media_attachments/files/113/516/630/720/076/713/original/27e3ef4b5923be14.png', 'preview_url': 'https://media.mastodon.de/cache/media_attachments/files/113/516/630/720/076/713/small/27e3ef4b5923be14.png', 'remote_url': 'https://s3.eu-central-2.wasabisys.com/mastodonworld/media_attachments/files/113/516/618/054/557/339/original/e79ab13ebc2729db.png', 'preview_remote_url': None, 'text_url': None, 'meta': {'focus': {'x': 0.0, 'y': 0.0}, 'original': {'width': 679, 'height': 364, 'size': '679x364', 'aspect': 1.8653846153846154}, 'small': {'width': 655, 'height': 351, 'size': '655x351', 'aspect': 1.8660968660968662}}, 'description': "McBride blasted Mace's legislation earlier this week, calling it “a blatant attempt from far right-wing extremists to distract from the fact that they have no real solutions to what Americans are facing.”

“We should be focused on bringing down the cost of housing, health care and child care, not manufacturing culture wars,” McBride said. “Delawareans sent me here to make the American dream more affordable and accessible and that’s what I'm focused on.”

Johnson’s decision to formally announce the new policy came after Mace was threatening to force a vote on the matter. [{'id': '113519152175790572', 'type': 'image', 'url': 'https://media.mastodon.de/cache/media_attachments/files/113/519/152/175/790/572/original/26c8026082fd7d23.jpeg', 'preview_url': 'https://media.mastodon.de/cache/media_attachments/files/113/519/152/175/790/572/small/26c8026082fd7d23.jpeg', 'remote_url': 'https://mastodon.tekdmn.me/system/media_attachments/files/113/519/106/437/235/258/original/a47b1e5c39aa2fee.jpeg', 'preview_remote_url': None, 'text_url': None, 'meta': {'focus': {'x': 0.02, 'y': 0.3}, 'original': {'width': 1247, 'height': 1663, 'size': '1247x1663', 'aspect': 0.7498496692723993}, 'small': {'width': 415, 'height': 554, 'size': '415x554', 'aspect': 0.7490974729241877}}, 'description': 'A Gossen Pilot light meter in it's plastic case with a blue fabric interior. The meter itself has two windows for setting the film ASA in the center (very tightly packed together, the values on the right window are "between" the values in the left window), an EV reading up at the top-right, and a single large scale for valid shutter/aperture combinations. The window at the bottom is quite dirty and dark, but it's just possible to make out the barest hint of a white line on the left and a yellow pointer on the right.', 'blurhash': 'UIGk%j~BR4xt~ASL57ELxTR*kXsm-;xu?GxZ'}, {'id': '113519152242317474', 'type': 'image', 'url': 'https://media.mastodon.de/cache/media_attachments/files/113/519/152/242/317/474/original/8a881133b16b22b1.jpeg', 'preview_url': 'https://media.mastodon.de/cache/media_attachments/files/113/519/152/242/317/474/small/8a881133b16b22b1.jpeg', 'remote_url': 'https://mastodon.tekdmn.me/system/media_attachments/files/113/519/106/443/448/423/original/ef2780e26328acd2.jpeg', 'preview_remote_url': None, 'text_url': None, 'meta': {'focus': {'x': 0.05, 'y': 0.02}, 'original': {'width': 1247, 'height': 1663, 'size': '1247x1663', 'aspect': 0.7498496692723993}, 'small': {'width': 415, 'height': 554, 'size': '415x554', 'aspect': 0.7490974729241877}}, 'description': 'A Sekonic model 38. This one has windows to read film sensitivity using both the ASA (black, right) and DIN (red, right) scales, the EV window is also marked LV, and at the top there's a "movie" scale that has f-numbers on the same ring as the "normal" scale has shutter speeds. The movie scale has marks for 64, 32, 24, 16 (highlighted), and 8. There's also a second metal disc in the center that has three points marked "CLOSED," "OPEN", "and "AMP," in red, blue, and black, respectively. The "OPEN" index is aligned with a red dot on the center.

On this meter instead of the needles protruding from the top of the device, they come from the bottom. A large, thin white line (sensor), a clear piece of plastic with a red "C" shape (setting), and a small white line and dot are seen etched into the back very, very near the zero position of the white needle.

The top (where the light cell is) has a metal cover with a small slit in it, and that cover is currently flipped out of the way.', 'blurhash': 'UGF=aO={rq-o_LENNGM|kQWBo|Rj.7ofxbxZ'}]

A beautiful mural with botanical motifs was sprayed/painted on the outside wall of a three-storey building. The mural is painted in light and dark green and shows a stone landscape with mountains in the background. A rare plant, "Gigas Gentiana punctata", a type of gentian, grows in the middle between the stones. It has tall, upright stems with spotted, pointed leaves and a crown of bright, densely packed, jagged flower buds. Golden insects buzz around it. An amphibian or lizard meanders along the base of the plant. Beautifully drawn and realized. It is reminiscent of old botanical books.\nInfo: The mural was painted in honor of the 90th anniversary of the Vitosha National Park.Vitosha is a mountain massif on the outskirts of the Bulgarian capital Sofia, it is known for its diverse ecosystems. This rare plant, Gentiana punctata, which is listed in the Bulgarian Red Book of Threatened Species, grows between huge stones.', 'blurhash': 'UnI#_jkCwdof~qxujut7wLt7S1ofniWVbFof'}]

Boethius: The seated figure, often interpreted as contemplative or despondent, represents the philosopher during his imprisonment. His skeletal frame and somber demeanor reflect suffering or introspection.

Philosophy: Personified as a woman, Philosophy appears compassionate yet authoritative, extending her hand in a gesture of explanation or guidance. She holds a staff or scepter, symbolizing wisdom, power, or knowledge.

Setting: The dark, enclosed room suggests confinement, corresponding to Boethius’s real-life imprisonment before his execution. The red drapery adds drama and focus to the interaction.

Themes: The painting embodies themes of human suffering, intellectual inquiry, and the transformative power of philosophy as a source of solace and enlightenment.
